header: Test vectors of type MacTest are intended for testing the

InvalidKeySize.description: The test vector contains a key with an invalid key size. Accepting such a key indicates an missing parameter verification.

ModifiedTag.description: The test vector contains a modified MAC. The purpose of the test is to check whether the verification fully checks the tag.

Pseudorandom.description: The test vector contains pseudorandomly generated inputs. The goal of the test vector is to check the correctness of the implementation for various sizes of the input parameters.
